description.2: The first appearance of Blue Shield! Dazzler teams up with the vigilante hero in his battle against a crime boss. It turns out that Dazzler knows more about Blue Shield than she thought…
description.7: Spider-Man vs. Nitro! Peter's strong, but even he can't out-muscle an exploding man!
description.8: Man-Elephant attempts to help the sheriff arrest She-Hulk!
description.9: Popular heavy metal musician Asmodeus Jones has quite a following … and not just by his fans! Can the Defenders interrupt the rocker's show before he can summon the demon Fashmina? Guest-starring Ghost Rider!
description.12: Strange dials up the notch on Clea's training, bestowing her with an object of prized power when she proves worthy. Then, the Sorcerer Supreme takes on Ikonn, the Lord of Illusions!
description.13: Dazzler has been captured and is stuck in a parallel dimension! Can she get herself out of this nightmare?
description.18: Darth Vader and Leia face off in a gambit involving X-Wing fighters the Rebellion sorely needs and priceless jewels!
description.19: Hydro-man is revealed to be behind Barney Wicker's assassination attempt; good thing Spider-Man got to Wicker in time! Sandman makes moves on Hydro-man's bar babe girlfriend, Sadie Frickett, leading to a super-powered bar brawl! The three reconcile, (both men decide to share Sadie), and tear up New York with a crime spree! Spider-Man's taking it to the docks, to take out his two most ferocious foes.
description.20: The Shadow Lord proves a worthy foe of the Avengers, perhaps because of his ancient powers and God Complex. The Avengers take the fight to Mount Vesuvius, where the entire team is in hot lava, along with the civilian population below.
description.21: While out on a date with the lovely Bernie Rosenthal, an explosion rocks the town, and Steve must spring into action! But when it's clear he's in over his an unlikely hero comes to his rescue!
description.22: Matt goes undercover and joins the Kingpin's gang so he can steal the info Fisk has collected on the underworld. Kingpin catches him in the act and beats him senseless. During the Kingpin's exchange with the men holding his wife, someone is apparently killed.
description.23: Ghost Rider meets a real ghost in the Apparition. Which being of the supernatural will win out?
description.24: Banner vs. Talbot reaches a climactic head when Talbot attacks Hulk atop a Japanese volcano!
description.25: Blacklash may have Iron Man's arms pinned but he's in for the ride of his life!
description.27: Spider-Woman's first night in a new city does not go as planned!
description.28: Loki and Karnilla join forces to take down Thor and Odin! Will Thor let a wintry wasteland prevent him from serving justice?
description.29: Uatu the Watcher recounts an alternate fate for Jean Grey. What if the X-woman had not been engulfed in the Phoenix's flames? Jean Grey is reborn alongside her fellow X-Men- but when the Dark Phoenix incurs its wrath, will her teammates be powerless to stop its destruction of Earth?
description.30: The FF and an entire city block are trapped in the Negative Zone! The team must battle Stygorr before he can destroy them as he has vowed. Meanwhile, the civilians caught in the Negative Zone grow restless, and begin to storm the Baxter Building!
description.31: The reserve X-Men attempt to save the team, but can they navigate Murderworld?
description.36: Daimon Hellstrom uses his satanic powers at the grave of Patsy Walker's mother and discovers a horrifying truth about the Six-Fingered Hand! Plus- the Defenders team up with Dracula in Transylvania to battle the demon known as Puishannt!
description.37: THE ZAPPING OF THE SHE-HULK! She-Hulk vs. the power company?
description.38: Retired in Japan, Kingpin sends his wife, Vanessa, to New York to hire Nelson and Murdock. Kingpin's plan is to turn state's evidence against the East Coast crime bosses.
description.39: The Night Rider returns! But is he friend or foe to Ghost Rider?
description.40: Banner teams up with the Russian Super Soldiers to thwart Phobos' plan. Can Phobos be stopped before the whole world suffers Chernobyl's fate?
description.42: Thor is confronted by the Dream Demon! Can the Thunderer uncover the demon's secrets before being consumed?
description.43: Firefrost reveals her and Ebon Seeker's origin. And it's a story too strange to describe! Guest-starring the Avengers!
description.44: The X-Men are coerced into rescuing Arcade from the maniacal grip of the tyrant Dr. Doom!
description.45: With the Smuggler's help, Spider-Man tries to expose the Maggia, a crime ring whose main currency is street narcotics.
description.50: A droid populated space station turns to anarchy as Rebel droids and Imperial droids fight for important schematics!
description.53: John Kowalski, a unique spirit, lures Man-Thing out of hiding…and leads him straight into a new jam with Andrew and Jennifer Kale!
description.58: Enter Doom! Doctor Doom wants to steal the Jewels of Doom. Little does he know, Dazzler is waiting for him to make a move…
description.59: Spider-Man plays local hero during the New York City Marathon, keeping runner and spectator alike safe. But when Madame Web's clairvoyance picks up an assassination plot, will Spider-Man uncover the perpetrator in time? Plus, is Debra Whitman getting back together with her hometown flame?
description.60: While visiting Wonder Man on a film shoot in Italy, the Beast and Wonder Man encounter the Shadow Lord. But why has the Shadow Lord materialized an entire city into the Mediterranean Sea?
description.61: While Captain America journeys through England, Bruce Banner, the Hulk's smart half is kidnapped. Does Banner's disappearance have anything to do with Captain America's investigation of the Matrix Eight?
description.63: She-Hulk saves a diabetic in a downward spiral!
description.64: Patsy Walker is kidnapped by the Gargoyle, and is used as the host for a demonic possession by him! The Defenders come to their teammate's aid, but what Patsy was offered while on "the other side" may change everything for her…
description.67: Clea has a dream about the "Black Oracle", and is summoned to be a part of the 'Sibyline Sisterhood'.
description.68: Dazzler has her first major gig and all her Super Hero friends are watching! When the Enchantress interrupts the performance and casts a spell on Dazzler, can all the heroes take her out?
description.69: Namor and Spider-Man are prime bait for the Frightful Four, and find themselves on the defensive when they must retreat for their lives. Namor returns to Atlantis, while Peter continues to search for his beautiful neighbor. But when Peter finally catches up to the mystery girl, he finds a beautiful villainess instead! Enter, Llyra of Atlantis!
description.70: An industrial spy seems to take his own life to ensure his secrets. However, in the aftermath of his bomb, the saboteur becomes the flame-wielding Pyron! Who is this mysterious Pyron, and what secrets about the Avengers was he willing to take to the grave?
description.71: Memories of past adventures bring Captain America to England's Greymoor Castle. Once there, Captain America must confront the ghosts of his past as he teams up with the mysterious Cedric Rawlings to stop villainous Druid!
description.72: The Millennium Falcon encounters problems while in hyperspace which causes them to enter another dimension!
description.75: Ka-Zar wonders if he should leave the jungle and join modern civilization, and ultimately discovers a vast new section of the Savage Land called Pangea!
description.77: Hulk finds himself in the radioactive "Forbidden Zone" in Russia, just as the Russian Super Soldiers arrive! A coincidental battle ensues!
description.78: Scott Lang-sans Ant-Man suit-battles alongside Iron against a trio of villains called the Raiders.
description.80: The first appearance of Siryn!  The sonic mutant who's been mainstays on X-Force and X-Factor makes her debut her as a villain alongside the nefarious Juggernaut and Black Tom Cassidy!
description.81: Firelord sees Thor on television and decides to avenge the death of the Air-Walker!
description.82: What if the mindless Man-Thing retained its human brain? The mind of Ted Sallis, trapped in the muck-monster's body! Plus, Captain America becomes President of the United States! Can a super hero deliver the diplomacy of a politician?
description.83: Know fear as D'Spayre will mean your end.  Can Man-Thing help Cyclops overcome his own fear and escape the death-grip of D'Spayre?
description.89: Lady Dorma is alive! Namor's former lover has been mysteriously resurrected...so why is an Atlantean army attacking London...with Namor leading the charge?
description.90: Howard and Bev wind up in New Orleans -- where Bev is kidnapped as an intended sacrifice by a voodoo cult!
description.93: Bullseye has a tumor in his brain that makes him see every day people as Daredevil, and he starts to kill them all.
description.94: Behold…the Orb! Feast your eyes on…the Orb! You won’t belive what you see when you view…the Orb! It's the Orb versus Ghost Rider in a battle of the spooky and macabre.
description.95: Bruce Banner begins his journey with two Arabs who believe they have uncovered a thousand year old myth!
description.96: As a satellite hurtles toward Earth, endangering millions of lives, Sunturion makes a decision to help Iron Man.
description.97: The stunning origin of the evil Witch-Woman is revealed! Not to mention she has Ghost Rider as her prisoner!
description.98: A scream that causes hallucinations forces Jessica to face every villian she's ever met!
description.99: Thor is in for some unexpected trouble when the Air-Walker finds him instead of the Silver Surfer! Will Thor have to clean up the Surfer's mess...and face Air-Walker alone?

3.text: Final issue! Man-Thing writer Chris Claremont explains why he can no longer pen the muck-monster’s tale…

4.text: Shang-Chi absconds to the south of France to recuperate, but trouble still seems to find him.

7.text: Spider-Man vs. Nitro! Peter's strong, but even he can't out-muscle an exploding man!

8.text: Man-Elephant attempts to help the sheriff arrest She-Hulk!

9.text: Popular heavy metal musician Asmodeus Jones has quite a following … and not just by his fans! Can the Defenders interrupt the rocker's show before he can summon the demon Fashmina? Guest-starring Ghost Rider!

14.text: Shang-Chi is forced into direct conflict with Yakuza.

23.text: Ghost Rider meets a real ghost in the Apparition. Which being of the supernatural will win out?

33.text: Power Man and Iron Fist are hired by Supremo, dictator of Terranueva, to take down a drug ring! But when the heroes discover their employer has captured Colleen Wing and is part of the drug trade himself, Power Man and Iron Fist bite the hand that feeds them!

34.text: Marc Spector’s lost his mind! What was left of it to lose, that is. Moon Knight fights the Werewolves after being infected with hallucinogenic water. Marlene succumbs to homicidal mania. How will Moon Knight handle the enemy in his home?

35.text: Ka-Zar and Shanna crash with the Pangean bird folk! New ground is crossed in their relationship.

36.text: Daimon Hellstrom uses his satanic powers at the grave of Patsy Walker's mother and discovers a horrifying truth about the Six-Fingered Hand! Plus- the Defenders team up with Dracula in Transylvania to battle the demon known as Puishannt!

37.text: THE ZAPPING OF THE SHE-HULK! She-Hulk vs. the power company?

39.text: The Night Rider returns! But is he friend or foe to Ghost Rider?

45.text: With the Smuggler's help, Spider-Man tries to expose the Maggia, a crime ring whose main currency is street narcotics.

47.text: Power Man and Iron Fist are hired to protect a group of mercenaries from the murderous Colonel Eschat! The Colonel is seeking out hits in order to protect his secret identity. District Attorney Blake Tower is in danger, and the Heroes for Hire are on the case!

48.text: Chicago’s gone mad! A gang laces the city’s water supply with violence-inducing hallucinogens. Moon Knight’s closest comrades are in grave danger. Will the questionably sane Moon Knight be able to save a certifiably insane Chicago?

49.text: Ka-Zar, Zabu, and Shanna are under attack from Pterons! Ka-Zar is faced with an unthinkable decision -- will he save Shanna or Queen Leanne?

52.text: Shang-Chi is once again haunted by his malicious father's past.

53.text: John Kowalski, a unique spirit, lures Man-Thing out of hiding…and leads him straight into a new jam with Andrew and Jennifer Kale!

63.text: She-Hulk saves a diabetic in a downward spiral!

64.text: Patsy Walker is kidnapped by the Gargoyle, and is used as the host for a demonic possession by him! The Defenders come to their teammate's aid, but what Patsy was offered while on "the other side" may change everything for her…

65.text: The Thing versus the maniacal machinations of the Puppet Master!

73.text: Power Man without super powers! When a villain from his past targets him for revenge, Luke Cage struggles to put up a fight! Meanwhile, Iron Fist and friends infiltrate the Bushmaster’s mansion to free Emma Burstein!

74.text: Moon Knight and co. travel to the Caribbean isles to hunt a voodoo monster. Beware the White Angel of Death, a night stalking zombie! Will another victim be taken in their sleep?

75.text: Ka-Zar wonders if he should leave the jungle and join modern civilization, and ultimately discovers a vast new section of the Savage Land called Pangea!

76.text: Ghost Rider meets Jack Russell…A.K.A. the Werewolf by Night!

85.text: Shang-Chi collaborates with karate champion and ex-C.I.A. agent Rufus Carter to take down a crew of pirates.

88.text: Scott Lang's ex-prison buddy Gus Sweezer crashes the scene with news on an exciting heist. Does this mean Ant-Man’s back to a life of crime? The Bugle sends Peter Parker on an investigative mission- one that leads straight to Taskmaster! Ant-Man and Spidey take on many villains in one man, as they steal back nuclear weapons from Taskmaster!

89.text: Lady Dorma is alive! Namor's former lover has been mysteriously resurrected...so why is an Atlantean army attacking London...with Namor leading the charge?

90.text: Howard and Bev wind up in New Orleans -- where Bev is kidnapped as an intended sacrifice by a voodoo cult!

91.text: When Kitty Pryde is left behind at the mansion alone, she's attached by a N'garai demon. Can the newest X-Man handle the villain all by her lonesome?

92.text: Hellcat and Man-Wolf fight She-Hulk in an effort to gain her help saving the Other Realm!

94.text: Behold…the Orb! Feast your eyes on…the Orb! You won’t believe what you see when you view…the Orb! It's the Orb versus Ghost Rider in a battle of the spooky and the macabre.
